cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DL 

This paper deals with expanding the functionality of software-defined networking (SDN) to include other network primitives, specifically storage and caching. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses identifying content for per-content policy, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for integrating different network elements, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DL (Machine Learning).
